      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my bathroom sink is dripping constantly and i cant stop it. it's one of those old ones where you turn the handle to tighten it. what do i need to fix it and how do i do it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You will likely need a set of plumbing tools, including slip-joint pliers or adjustable wrenches, to tighten or replace the internal cartridge or linear washer inside the handle assembly. Carefully remove the whip cord connecting the handle to the valve underneath, apply a new sealed washer or adjust the existing washers to stop water flow, and reinstall everything securely. Since the issue involves an internal component, you may also need a new hot and cold washers depending on the specific model, so checking the manufacturer's parts diagram first is recommended.",
